# Project Rules

1. Code Review Before Changes
   - Always review existing changes made by the user before suggesting or making new changes
   - Do not remove or modify code that the user has intentionally added or modified
   - Only make changes to code that the user explicitly requests to be changed
   - If unsure about existing changes, ask the user for clarification

2. Code Consistency
   - Maintain consistent styling and formatting across all files
   - Follow the existing code patterns and conventions
   - Keep the codebase clean and organized

3. Documentation
   - Document any significant changes or new features
   - Keep comments clear and meaningful
   - Update relevant documentation when making changes

4. Testing
   - Ensure all changes work as expected
   - Test across different screen sizes and devices
   - Verify that existing functionality is not broken

5. Communication
   - Be clear about proposed changes
   - Explain the reasoning behind suggestions
   - Ask for clarification when needed 